'''Joe Shmoe''' is one of the most commonly used fictional names. Due to the [[rhyme]], it is an easy to remember name, often used by teachers to assist their students in learning a concept with an [[anecdote]]. This name was probably derived from a person scornfully responding to a friend who said "Joe will get you". The person may have then replied "Joe Schmoe" advertising his apathy.

